            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a generous drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>pepper strips</strong>, <strong>onion</strong> and <strong>sliced chicken</strong> to the pan with the <strong>BBQ spice blend</strong></p><p>Cook for 8-10 min or until the vegetables have softened and the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!) – this is your <strong>smoky 'n' sweet BBQ chicken fajita filling</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
